here ya go. (chained ternary operators)
```
function lookUp(firstName, prop){
  var contact = contacts.filter(function(x) { return x["firstName"] == firstName })
  return contact.length < 1 ? "No such contact" : contact[0][prop] != null ? contact[0][prop] : "No such property"
}
```

@BenjaminDowns a few suggestions with regards to your solution:

  1. Try to use the strict comparison operators `===` and/or `!==` instead of the lax comparison operators, you will experience less bugs in your code.
  1. If you are doing a simple if/else check, ternary operations (e.g. `condition ? if_true_execute_this : else_execute_this`) may make your code easier to read/understand

